      • getPath

        public java.lang.String getPath()
        Returns the file path (in system independent format) affected by this event.

        Note that the path might be cached, thus can become out-of-date if requested later, asynchronously from the event dispatching procedure (e.g. event.getPath() can become not equal to event.getFile().getPath()).

      • computePath

        protected abstract java.lang.String computePath()

      • getFile

        public abstract VirtualFile getFile()
        Returns the VirtualFile which this event belongs to. In some cases it may be null - it is not guaranteed that there is such file.

        NB: Use this method with caution, because VFileCreateEvent.getFile() needs VirtualFile.findChild(String) which may be a performance leak.
